entry.def: If you describe something as dinky, you mean that it is attractive and appealing, usually because it is quite small and well-designed.

example.ex: Darby drove a dinky old Fiat sports car.
example.tran: 达比开着一辆漂亮的老式菲亚特跑车。

entry.def: If you describe something as dinky, you mean that it is small and unimportant.

example.ex: The hotels are full up, and the guests have had to go to this dinky little motel way out on Stewart Avenue.
example.tran: 宾馆已经客满了，客人们不得不到斯图尔特街上这家偏远的小汽车旅馆里来。
